Why this copy exists
--------------------
The upstream action repository publishes a very large number of git tags,
which prevents Renovate from enumerating its releases and bumping the action.
By hosting the action definition locally and referencing the upstream checkov
Docker image (docker://ghcr.io/bridgecrewio/checkov:<tag>) directly, Renovate's
built-in github-actions manager can keep the checkov version up to date via the
`runs.image` reference in action.yml.

